WEBVTT

00:17.952 --> 00:19.284
Maggie:
<i>We've met before.</i>

00:19.286 --> 00:20.986
Dandy:
I don't think so.

00:20.988 --> 00:23.455
I never forget a pretty face.

00:23.457 --> 00:25.958
Your voice sounds so familiar,

00:25.960 --> 00:28.360
I can almost place it.

00:29.830 --> 00:31.463
Is that enough to start?
(laughs)

00:31.465 --> 00:33.966
For five dollars,
you can ask me anything.

00:33.968 --> 00:36.668
I've had a few recent...

00:36.670 --> 00:39.972
Misadventures
with the fairer sex.

00:39.974 --> 00:40.973
You're a heartbreaker.

00:40.975 --> 00:42.808
That's not hard to see.

00:42.810 --> 00:45.644
I've hurt someone badly.

00:45.646 --> 00:48.981
And the person
i always counted on for help...

00:48.983 --> 00:51.884
Can't help anymore.

00:51.886 --> 00:54.887
And you're afraid
this time you'll have to pay.

01:09.870 --> 01:11.703
Avon calling.

01:11.705 --> 01:13.505
Is the lady
of the house available?

01:13.507 --> 01:16.008
Do come in.

01:16.010 --> 01:18.043
Mother would love
to have some company.

01:18.045 --> 01:19.411
Oh...

01:22.917 --> 01:24.983
(quietly impressed):
Oh...!

01:27.721 --> 01:30.089
(dandy humming "if you're
happy and you know it")

01:47.041 --> 01:49.308
Now you're my puppet mother.

01:52.213 --> 01:54.079
Let's play a game.

01:54.081 --> 01:57.116
Mother, you be dot.

01:58.719 --> 02:00.953
Avon lady,
whose name i don't know,

02:00.955 --> 02:04.890
You get to play the part
of bette!

02:04.892 --> 02:07.926
(dandy laughing)

02:07.928 --> 02:09.928
Maggie:
<i>You can rest easy.</i>

02:09.930 --> 02:12.898
The ball is clear as day.

02:12.900 --> 02:16.468
Your indiscretion will
soon be forgotten.

02:16.470 --> 02:18.070
What about, uh,

02:18.072 --> 02:20.005
Trouble from my past?

02:22.476 --> 02:24.743
Oh, there is someone.

02:24.745 --> 02:27.279
A dark cloud on the horizon.

02:27.281 --> 02:30.749
There will be rain,
but... It'll pass.

02:30.751 --> 02:33.085
And you'll go on
just like before,

02:33.087 --> 02:34.586
Breaking hearts.

02:34.588 --> 02:36.121
I can't tell you

02:36.123 --> 02:38.657
What it means
to hear those words.

02:38.659 --> 02:40.759
(dandy laughs)

02:40.761 --> 02:43.162
You are my savior.

02:48.936 --> 02:52.237
A hundred thank-you's,
esmeralda.

02:53.274 --> 02:55.274
Please...

02:55.276 --> 02:57.876
Come back for a reading anytime.

03:00.147 --> 03:02.948
You have true talent.

03:02.950 --> 03:05.184
It would be a shame

03:05.186 --> 03:07.953
To waste the powers
inside of you.

03:07.955 --> 03:10.022
(anxious laugh)

03:27.374 --> 03:30.142
Ima, i've never seen
anybody like anything

03:30.144 --> 03:32.477
More than you
and a mouthful of food.

03:32.479 --> 03:34.813
(both laugh)

03:34.815 --> 03:38.317
I want to see it again.

03:38.319 --> 03:40.552
Oh, you're
too good to me, jimmy.

03:40.554 --> 03:44.022
You find the twins yet?

03:44.024 --> 03:46.792
I see you been doing
a lot of looking.

03:48.395 --> 03:51.230
I've been busy feeding ima.

03:51.232 --> 03:52.364
Eat up, baby.

03:52.366 --> 03:53.565
If you want it long and hard,

03:53.567 --> 03:55.567
I need you soft and wide.

03:55.569 --> 03:57.536
(both laugh)

03:57.538 --> 04:01.406
Jesus, jimmy,
you are stinking drunk.

04:01.408 --> 04:03.442
(whistling nearby)

04:09.350 --> 04:12.351
Jimmy (shouts drunkenly):
You...!

04:12.353 --> 04:15.020
What'd you do
with the twins?

04:15.022 --> 04:16.855
Last i saw, they were with you.

04:16.857 --> 04:18.223
But if you see bette and dot,

04:18.225 --> 04:19.424
I'd be happy
to take them back.

04:19.426 --> 04:20.525
No questions asked.

04:20.527 --> 04:21.560
I would never let them near you.

04:21.562 --> 04:23.228
I know exactly who you are.

04:23.230 --> 04:25.264
You were behind that mask.

04:25.266 --> 04:27.699
You were the other clown.

04:27.701 --> 04:29.201
Are you with this drunk?

04:29.203 --> 04:30.702
Hey, come on, jimmy.

04:30.704 --> 04:32.070
Let's stand to one side,
let this...

04:32.072 --> 04:34.373
No! No!

04:34.375 --> 04:36.041
You're a murderer.

04:36.043 --> 04:37.876
(groans)
there's nothing worse

04:37.878 --> 04:39.444
Than an alcoholic
with bad hygiene.

04:39.446 --> 04:41.246
Such a waste.

04:41.248 --> 04:43.382
I'm gonna put you away if
it's the last thing i do!

04:43.384 --> 04:47.386
God, you're pathetic.
(jimmy groans)

04:47.388 --> 04:50.422
And if you hadn't stolen
the twins from me,

04:50.424 --> 04:53.292
I would leave you
here in your filth.

04:53.294 --> 04:56.228
But you took away my
last chance at happiness.

04:56.230 --> 04:58.297
And for that,

04:58.299 --> 05:00.632
I must have revenge.

05:02.236 --> 05:05.237
I'm your god, jimmy.

05:05.239 --> 05:10.142
And i've decided
that you need to suffer.

05:10.144 --> 05:12.911
I'm going to destroy you

05:12.913 --> 05:15.247
And everything you love.

05:15.249 --> 05:16.648
Oh...

05:17.751 --> 05:20.819
It will be so much fun.

06:48.008 --> 06:50.108
(persistent knocking on door)
bette:
<i>What do we do?</i>

06:51.712 --> 06:52.911
Oh,<i> meine liebchen!</i>

06:52.913 --> 06:54.546
Thank goodness
we have found you.

06:54.548 --> 06:56.248
But look at this.

06:57.751 --> 07:00.352
Living like animals.

07:00.354 --> 07:01.420
But how wise of ethel

07:01.422 --> 07:03.255
To have hidden you away.

07:03.257 --> 07:05.357
Where is ethel?
What's going on?

07:05.359 --> 07:07.058
There's a mob out there
hunting freaks.

07:07.060 --> 07:09.261
Yes. More than a mob,
the entire town.

07:09.263 --> 07:12.063
These floridian rubes have
finally turned against us.

07:12.065 --> 07:13.432
No freak is safe.

07:13.434 --> 07:16.201
Ethel was the first to go.

07:16.203 --> 07:17.202
Ethel's dead?

07:17.204 --> 07:18.937
They tore her head off.

07:20.374 --> 07:22.073
Imagine what a crazy mob
would do

07:22.075 --> 07:24.075
With your two heads.
How did you find us?

07:24.077 --> 07:26.445
It wasn't difficult.

07:26.447 --> 07:27.712
I have my connections.

07:27.714 --> 07:28.713
Stanley:
<i>Are you sure she left a note?</i>

07:28.715 --> 07:29.748
Elsa:
<i>Yes! Why would</i>

07:29.750 --> 07:30.782
<i>She make up such a thing?</i>

07:30.784 --> 07:33.351
She was about
to plug me good.

07:34.388 --> 07:36.888
Ah, here!

07:36.890 --> 07:40.459
A motor hotel
in west palm beach.

07:40.461 --> 07:42.294
That's where
she stashed the twins.

07:42.296 --> 07:44.629
She instructs jimmy
to go find them.

07:46.967 --> 07:49.401
Stanley:<i> We have to get you</i>
<i>someplace safe.</i>

07:49.403 --> 07:51.470
But not back to the camp.

07:51.472 --> 07:52.404
No, no, no, no.

07:52.406 --> 07:54.406
But we have a place and a plan.

07:54.408 --> 07:57.309
I don't believe you. Why should
i trust anything you say?

07:57.311 --> 08:00.111
Because i have done
what you asked.

08:00.113 --> 08:02.647
The surgeon you wanted,
the one who separated

08:02.649 --> 08:03.815
The brodie twins...

08:03.817 --> 08:05.417
He is on his way down here.

08:05.419 --> 08:07.919
Your every wish is about

08:07.921 --> 08:09.488
To come true.

08:16.930 --> 08:18.930
Maggie: We already
looked over here.

08:18.932 --> 08:20.932
All we did was call out
"bette and dot"

08:20.934 --> 08:22.501
A couple of times.

08:22.503 --> 08:24.503
Well, hello.

08:24.505 --> 08:25.470
Maggie:
Who are you?

08:25.472 --> 08:27.606
What do you want?

08:27.608 --> 08:30.108
I came to see miss desiree.

08:30.110 --> 08:32.644
The most beautiful woman

08:32.646 --> 08:35.514
In the world.

08:35.516 --> 08:37.516
Well, you come back
at show time,

08:37.518 --> 08:38.850
Like everyone else.

08:38.852 --> 08:40.652
Uh, but we have a rendezvous...

08:40.654 --> 08:42.621
You better scram, pal.

08:42.623 --> 08:44.956
Or you'll have a rendezvous
with a black eye.

08:44.958 --> 08:47.292
I'm a big girl, maggie.

08:47.294 --> 08:49.361
Go on.

08:50.531 --> 08:52.564
Oh.

08:53.500 --> 08:54.866
Mmm.

08:54.868 --> 08:57.502
I'm sorry, but i
could not stay away.

08:57.504 --> 08:59.304
Mm-mm.

08:59.306 --> 09:01.540
You better get
ahold of yourself,

09:01.542 --> 09:05.043
Angus t. Jefferson.

09:08.715 --> 09:11.049
Maggie:
<i>Who was that?</i>

09:11.051 --> 09:13.985
My beau.

09:13.987 --> 09:16.488
And you say anything, you gonna
be the one with the black eye.

09:16.490 --> 09:19.057
(passionate moaning nearby)
i wouldn't dream of it.

09:21.328 --> 09:23.562
(both laugh)

09:27.501 --> 09:29.634
Ain't that a sight?

09:31.338 --> 09:32.370
Are you... Serious?

09:32.372 --> 09:34.506
Really?

09:34.508 --> 09:36.174
Shit!

09:36.176 --> 09:39.010
Goddamn it, i was
so close to a nut!

09:39.012 --> 09:40.579
(laughs)

09:40.581 --> 09:42.514
Well, let's leave the pigs
to their rutting.

09:42.516 --> 09:44.516
Shall we?

09:44.518 --> 09:46.351
Sure knows how
to ruin a party.

09:46.353 --> 09:49.521
Ima: Let her go, honey.
You got me now.

09:49.523 --> 09:51.222
He'll put it in anyone!

09:51.224 --> 09:52.524
He's drunk!

09:52.526 --> 09:54.025
Leave her out of this!

09:54.027 --> 09:55.026
She's nice.

09:55.028 --> 09:56.728
And soft.

09:56.730 --> 09:58.430
(scoffs)

09:58.432 --> 09:59.531
No, don't go, don't go!

09:59.533 --> 10:02.367
Don't touch me,
you asshole!

10:02.369 --> 10:05.036
She begs me to touch her!

10:05.038 --> 10:06.738
Look at these knockers!

10:06.740 --> 10:10.208
And i swear, she tastes
like a lemon-lime lollipop!

10:10.210 --> 10:12.744
You keep your mitts off him
or i'll jump on your ass

10:12.746 --> 10:14.779
And i'll flatten you
like a cracker!

10:14.781 --> 10:17.549
(scoffs)
you're nothing!

10:17.551 --> 10:19.618
You could be a pillow!
A donut!

10:19.620 --> 10:20.552
A sock!

10:20.554 --> 10:23.655
Jimmy...?

10:25.592 --> 10:27.926
(retching, vomiting)

10:27.928 --> 10:30.562
Myrna:
<i>You did?</i>

10:30.564 --> 10:32.897
My goodness!
What-what did it taste like?

10:32.899 --> 10:35.400
I don't know-- like skin, but

10:35.402 --> 10:36.635
Softer and saltier, i think.

10:36.637 --> 10:39.571
You are so liberal.

10:39.573 --> 10:41.640
Well, all i know

10:41.642 --> 10:43.775
Is that someone got
a new stove delivered

10:43.777 --> 10:46.478
From sears and roebuck
this afternoon.

10:46.480 --> 10:48.680
(all laugh)

10:50.083 --> 10:51.950
Are you okay?

10:51.952 --> 10:53.652
He's drunk.

10:53.654 --> 10:56.454
He kept... Missing.

10:56.456 --> 10:58.657
I just paid him and left.

11:01.428 --> 11:02.827
Who's next?

11:04.598 --> 11:05.764
Goddamn starving.

11:05.766 --> 11:08.633
Ethel:
You're disgusting.

11:08.635 --> 11:10.902
I'm rolling over in my grave.

11:13.106 --> 11:15.373
Ma?

11:17.611 --> 11:19.678
I gave birth to you,

11:19.680 --> 11:21.179
Squatting by an oak tree.

11:21.181 --> 11:22.781
Nearly killed me.

11:22.783 --> 11:24.282
The worrying,

11:24.284 --> 11:26.451
The sacrifices,
and all for what?

11:26.453 --> 11:28.520
I'm sorry, ma.

11:30.624 --> 11:33.124
Why'd you do that to yourself?

11:33.126 --> 11:35.627
Why didn't you come
to me for help?

11:35.629 --> 11:37.295
I didn't have
much time left anyway.

11:37.297 --> 11:39.464
No one was gonna preserve
ethel darling

11:39.466 --> 11:41.666
And keep her around
past her time.

11:41.668 --> 11:43.802
How did you store leftovers
in your day, ethel?

11:43.804 --> 11:46.404
Leftovers?

11:47.708 --> 11:48.640
Is that what these are for?

11:48.642 --> 11:51.309
Keeping old food fresh?

11:51.311 --> 11:53.011
I'm confused.

11:53.013 --> 11:54.012
I need you!

11:54.014 --> 11:56.715
When you protect the past,

11:56.717 --> 11:58.483
You lose the future.

11:58.485 --> 11:59.684
(muffled sobbing)

11:59.686 --> 12:02.053
You're wasting
your life grieving over me.

12:02.055 --> 12:05.523
You were supposed
to redeem our sorry line.

12:05.525 --> 12:06.825
(chuckles)

12:06.827 --> 12:08.059
To think,

12:08.061 --> 12:10.328
I wasted all my hopes
and dreams

12:10.330 --> 12:11.329
On another

12:11.331 --> 12:13.665
No-good drunk,

12:13.667 --> 12:15.500
(whispering):
Like his father.

12:15.502 --> 12:16.735
Elaine:
Oh, ethel,

12:16.737 --> 12:17.736
You're a delight.

12:17.738 --> 12:19.170
Jimmy (muffled):
I'm so sorry!

12:19.172 --> 12:21.906
I'm so sorry.

12:26.346 --> 12:27.746
I think you need to leave.

12:35.522 --> 12:38.089
(sighs)

12:38.091 --> 12:40.391
¶ what a wonderful holiday ¶

12:40.393 --> 12:42.861
¶ with bells on every sleigh ¶

12:42.863 --> 12:46.898
¶ and voices full
of happy cheer ¶

12:46.900 --> 12:48.600
(muttering)

12:48.602 --> 12:50.368
¶ bringing all the good luck
and health ¶

12:50.370 --> 12:52.704
(lock clicks)
¶ you'd ever wish yourself... ¶

12:52.706 --> 12:55.540
I am so sorry, ladies.

12:55.542 --> 12:57.375
(doorbell rings)
maybe we should eat.

12:57.377 --> 12:59.444
(knocking on door)

13:01.281 --> 13:02.781
Should we call the police?

13:03.950 --> 13:05.583
No.

13:05.585 --> 13:08.119
It's okay.

13:08.121 --> 13:09.721
Hello.

13:09.723 --> 13:11.222
Am i interrupting?

13:11.224 --> 13:13.892
(sighs)
my, that dress is
a magical color.

13:13.894 --> 13:15.727
What is that, periwinkle?

13:15.729 --> 13:17.796
Lana lobell calls it
"spanish sky."

13:17.798 --> 13:19.597
That's remarkable.

13:19.599 --> 13:20.965
(chuckles)
i'm sorry.

13:20.967 --> 13:22.734
My car just broke down.

13:22.736 --> 13:25.069
Would you mind if i came in
and borrowed your telephone

13:25.071 --> 13:26.571
To call the auto club?

13:26.573 --> 13:27.739
I'm happy to pay you
for the call.

13:27.741 --> 13:29.774
(chuckles)
nonsense. Come in.

13:29.776 --> 13:31.876
Thank you.

13:55.769 --> 13:57.602
Bette:
Dot, look.

13:57.604 --> 13:58.937
Our diaries.

13:58.939 --> 14:00.805
I have so missed my writing.

14:00.807 --> 14:02.607
I thought you would.

14:02.609 --> 14:03.942
So i brought some
of your things,

14:03.944 --> 14:05.343
And, well, some of mine,

14:05.345 --> 14:07.645
To make the place
seem more homey.

14:07.647 --> 14:09.948
How long do you expect us
to stay here?

14:09.950 --> 14:11.649
Oh, not for long.

14:11.651 --> 14:13.685
Just until the doctor arrives.

14:13.687 --> 14:15.687
Well, i don't understand.

14:15.689 --> 14:17.856
He's gonna operate on us here?

14:17.858 --> 14:20.825
Bette:
Oh, god.

14:20.827 --> 14:23.494
Oh, no, i can't.

14:23.496 --> 14:25.029
No!
Elsa:<i> I can't.</i>

14:25.031 --> 14:27.365
No. I took those girls in.

14:27.367 --> 14:29.868
I promised to protect them.

14:29.870 --> 14:32.804
And now what? Murder?

14:32.806 --> 14:34.472
I love my monsters.

14:34.474 --> 14:35.807
I truly do.

14:35.809 --> 14:37.308
No, of course you do.

14:37.310 --> 14:39.143
A heart as passionate
as yours,

14:39.145 --> 14:40.979
That gives so much on the stage,

14:40.981 --> 14:44.649
Cannot help but feel empathy
for god's cast-offs.

14:44.651 --> 14:45.817
In fact,

14:45.819 --> 14:47.485
I came
to the same conclusion myself.

14:47.487 --> 14:48.987
What conclusion?

14:48.989 --> 14:50.822
I realized you were right
all along.

14:50.824 --> 14:52.891
The best way to send
those girls off in style

14:52.893 --> 14:54.993
Is to give them
exactly what they want.

14:54.995 --> 14:57.729
So i made a few calls
to hollywood.

14:57.731 --> 14:59.530
To hollywood?
Yeah.

14:59.532 --> 15:02.066
I was, uh, chummy with
greer garson's dermatologist.

15:02.068 --> 15:04.068
She happens to be close
personal friends

15:04.070 --> 15:05.870
With a chicago doctor,

15:05.872 --> 15:07.705
This guy who separated
the twins.

15:07.707 --> 15:10.675
I called him up
on the telephone.

15:10.677 --> 15:12.010
You called him?
Yeah.

15:12.012 --> 15:13.411
If the twins are separated,

15:13.413 --> 15:15.079
They can be
no more trouble to you.

15:15.081 --> 15:18.016
It's a win-win-win.

15:18.018 --> 15:19.884
We go off to california.

15:19.886 --> 15:23.421
The girls can stay here to live
their two separate lives.

15:26.860 --> 15:29.861
Elsa:
<i>What's this table doing here?</i>

15:29.863 --> 15:31.429
This is for
the initial examination.

15:31.431 --> 15:33.731
The actual surgery will
take place in the hospital.

15:33.733 --> 15:35.733
Dr. Sugar is seeing to all
the arrangements now.

15:35.735 --> 15:37.035
It's all very...

15:37.037 --> 15:38.770
(whispering):
Hush-hush.

15:38.772 --> 15:41.940
Uh, you'll be transported there
under cover of night,

15:41.942 --> 15:43.241
Of course.

15:43.243 --> 15:44.876
How much is this gonna cost us?

15:44.878 --> 15:45.944
Not a penny.
Since he worked

15:45.946 --> 15:47.111
With the brodie twins,

15:47.113 --> 15:49.047
Dr. Sugar is fascinated
by your case.

15:49.049 --> 15:50.381
One of those twins died.

15:50.383 --> 15:53.084
That's true,
but dr. Sugar assured me

15:53.086 --> 15:56.955
That that casualty was due
to a very rare infection,

15:56.957 --> 15:59.757
And he's now perfected
his technique.

15:59.759 --> 16:01.459
So we both can live.

16:02.729 --> 16:03.895
Well, just imagine it, bette.

16:03.897 --> 16:06.898
You can go to the movies
any time you want.

16:06.900 --> 16:09.901
Sing along to the radio
and dance all night.

16:09.903 --> 16:11.903
With one leg.
I explained to dr. Sugar

16:11.905 --> 16:14.739
That you each had
your own heart and lungs.

16:14.741 --> 16:16.808
He said there's no reason

16:16.810 --> 16:18.977
Why you can't be split
down the middle.

16:18.979 --> 16:21.412
(gasps)
bette, enough!

16:21.414 --> 16:24.415
After all these years together,
i want my freedom.

16:24.417 --> 16:25.616
A chance at love

16:25.618 --> 16:27.318
Like a normal woman.

16:27.320 --> 16:28.987
How can you
not understand that?

16:28.989 --> 16:30.421
No.

16:30.423 --> 16:31.956
No, i won't.

16:31.958 --> 16:33.758
I won't do it.

16:33.760 --> 16:35.793
It's barbaric.

16:35.795 --> 16:38.596
Nonsense.
They'll anesthetize you girls,

16:38.598 --> 16:40.498
So you won't feel a thing.

16:40.500 --> 16:42.633
Elsa:
Your sister's right.

16:42.635 --> 16:44.635
You need your own lives.

